Condition : 10 - Travel Plan - Prior to the occupation of the development hereby permitted, a Travel Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The Plan shall follow the current 'Travel Plan Development Control Guidance' issued by TfL and shall include:
  (i) Targets for sustainable travel arrangements;
  (ii) Effective measures for the on-going monitoring of the Plan;
  (iii) A commitment to delivering the Plan objectives for a period of at least 5 years from the first occupation of the development;
  (iv) Effective mechanisms to achieve the objectives of the Plan by both present and future occupiers of the development.
The development shall be implemented only on accordance with the approved Travel Plan.

Condition : 11 - Working Method Statement - Development shall not commence until a working method statement has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority to accommodate:

   (i) Parking of vehicles of site workers and visitors;
   (ii) Loading and unloading of plant and materials;
   (iii) Storage of construction plant and materials;
   (iv) Wheel cleaning facilities
   (v) Control of dust, smell and other effluvia;
   (vi) Control of surface water run-off.

No development shall be carried out except in full accordance with the approved method statement.

Condition : 22 - Flood Risk Assessment - The development shall be carried and implemented in accordance with the submitted and approved revised Flood Risk Assessment and Addendum by Ramboll Ltd (Ref: 1620012561 - Revision/Issue No.6, dated 19th October 2022) and the following mitigation measures it specifies:
"	Flood Risk Resistance measures/property Level Protection including alteration and raising to the vehicular ramp at the southeast of the Site, and reinforcements to the existing wall along the east of the Site;
"	Green Roofs; 
"	Permeable Pavements; 
"	Trees; and 
"	Rills and Channels.
These mitigation measures shall be fully implemented prior to occupation and subsequently in accordance with the schemes timing/phasing arrangements. The measures details above shall be retained and maintained by the site owner or their appointed management/maintenance company throughout the lifetime of the development.
Reason: To reduce the risk of flooding to and from the proposed development and future occupant in accordance with NPPF Chapter 13, London Plan (2021) Policy SI 12, SI 13. Merton Core Strategy (2011) Policy CS16 and Merton Sites and Policies Plan (2015) policies DMF1 and DMF2.
